Preheat your oven to 200°C.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a #large frying pan{} on medium-high heat. Once hot, add the @diced chicken breast{260%g} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Fry, turning frequently until the chicken is browned all over, ~{3-5%minutes}.
> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands after handling raw chicken and its packaging.

While the chicken is cooking, halve, peel and chop the @red onion{1} into small pieces.

Peel and grate the @garlic cloves{2} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Drain and rinse the @black beans{1} in a #sieve{}, put half of them into a #bowl{} and roughly mash with a #fork{}. Add the remaining whole beans to the bowl.

Drain the @sweetcorn{150%g} in a sieve.

Once the chicken is browned, add the onion to the pan.

Fry, stirring frequently, until the onion has softened, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Stir in the @Mexican style spice mix{1}, sweetcorn and half the garlic. Cook, stirring, for ~{1%minute}.
> TIP: Add less spice if you don't like heat.

Pour in the @tomato passata{1}, @water{200%ml} for the sauce, @chicken stock paste{15%g} and black beans (whole and mashed).

Season the sauce with salt, pepper and @sugar{1/4%tsp}.

Bring to the boil, stirring continuously, then reduce the heat to medium.

Simmer until the mixture is thick and the chicken is cooked, ~{6-8%minutes}. Stir every 2 mins or so.
> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

While the stew cooks, grate the @mature cheddar cheese{30%g}.

== Garlic Ciabatta ==

Meanwhile, in a small bowl, mix together the remaining garlic and @olive oil{1.5%tsp} for the garlic bread.

Cut each @ciabatta{2} in half. Place on a #baking tray{}, spread the garlic oil on the cut side and season with salt and pepper.

Bake until golden, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Once the stew is cooked, stir in the @baby spinach{100%g} a handful at a time until wilted and piping hot, ~{1-2%minutes}.
> TIP: Add a splash of water if needed.

== To Serve ==

Remove the pan from the heat, taste and add salt and pepper if you feel it needs it.

Serve in bowls with the cheese scattered on top and the garlic ciabatta alongside. Enjoy!

> STEP 1 MOD: If you've chosen to get diced chicken breast instead of chicken thigh, cook the recipe in
> the same way the instructions tell you to cook the chicken thigh.